Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.91,0:00:16.41,Default,,0,0,0,,威尔·史密斯：下赢国际象棋你需要什么？\N{\fs15\}WILL SMITH: What do you need to win a game of chess?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.45,0:00:21.48,Default,,0,0,0,,耐心  巧妙的战术  丰富的想象力\N{\fs15\}Patience, clever tactics, loads of imagination.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.52,0:00:22.72,Default,,0,0,0,,你看起来很紧张\N{\fs15\}You look nervous.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.75,0:00:25.09,Default,,0,0,0,,什么使我们成为人类\N{\fs15\}What makes us human
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.12,0:00:28.86,Default,,0,0,0,,是我们脑袋里的三镑重的糊状物\N{\fs15\}is the squishy triple-pounder inside our heads.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.86,0:00:31.83,Default,,0,0,0,,“将军”\N{\fs15\}Check.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.86,0:00:34.06,Default,,0,0,0,,它让我们把我们的朋友“将死”\N{\fs15\}It lets us checkmate our friends,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.10,0:00:35.73,Default,,0,0,0,,建造摩天大楼\N{\fs15\}build skyscrapers,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.76,0:00:39.84,Default,,0,0,0,,把我们中的一些人送到太空\N{\fs15\}and lift a special few of us into space.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.74,0:00:50.61,Default,,0,0,0,,八名宇航员  他们在的太空时间超过1000天\N{\fs15\}Eight astronauts with over 1,000 days in space between them
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.65,0:00:53.62,Default,,0,0,0,,能告诉我们上面的情况怎么样\N{\fs15\}can tell us how being up there
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.65,0:00:57.65,Default,,0,0,0,,帮助他们真正理解下面发生的事情\N{\fs15\}helped them to truly understand what goes on down here.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.09,0:01:02.02,Default,,0,0,0,,杰夫·霍夫曼：从太空中你可以看到全局\N{\fs15\}JEFF HOFFMAN: From space you get the big picture.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.06,0:01:04.59,Default,,0,0,0,,你真的看到了人类文明\N{\fs15\}You really see human civilization
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.63,0:01:08.13,Default,,0,0,0,,在你下方展开\N{\fs15\}spread out below you.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.16,0:01:09.63,Default,,0,0,0,,妮可·斯托特：据我们所知\N{\fs15\}NICOLE STOTT: As far as we know,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.67,0:01:14.47,Default,,0,0,0,,宇宙中没有其他生物像我们一样\N{\fs15\}there's nobody else like us out there in the universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.50,0:01:16.87,Default,,0,0,0,,杰里·林格：我能理解的唯一原因是\N{\fs15\}JERRY LINENGER: The only reason I'm able to comprehend
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.91,0:01:19.91,Default,,0,0,0,,地球不可思议的复杂性\N{\fs15\}the incredible complexity of the Earth
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.94,0:01:25.88,Default,,0,0,0,,是因为我的大脑非常复杂\N{\fs15\}is because I have an incredibly complex brain inside my head.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.91,0:01:28.88,Default,,0,0,0,,我们是这个星球上唯一的\N{\fs15\}We are the only species on this planet
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.92,0:01:33.62,Default,,0,0,0,,可以在我们的头脑中构建现实\N{\fs15\}that can construct realities in our mind
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.66,0:01:35.76,Default,,0,0,0,,然后去建造它的物种\N{\fs15\}and then go actually build it.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.99,0:01:40.63,Default,,0,0,0,,史密斯：但30亿年来\N{\fs15\}SMITH: But for three billion years,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.63,0:01:41.00,标题,,0,0,0,,{\pos(320,220)\fad(500,500)}国 家 地 理 {\fs10\b0}倾 情 呈 现
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.66,0:01:43.17,Default,,0,0,0,,生物甚至没有大脑\N{\fs15\}life didn't even have a brain.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.67,0:01:47.90,Default,,0,0,0,,梅尔文：关于我们大脑进化的故事\N{\fs15\}MELVIN: The story of how our mind evolved
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.94,0:01:50.14,Default,,0,0,0,,在这一块奇怪的石头上\N{\fs15\}on this one strange rock
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.17,0:01:54.51,Default,,0,0,0,,是偶然  巧合和不可能的偶然之一\N{\fs15\}is one of chance, coincidence and impossible odds.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.55,0:02:03.69,Default,,0,0,0,,史密斯：我要告诉你最不可思议的地方\N{\fs15\}SMITH: I am going to tell you about the most incredible place.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.72,0:02:06.52,Default,,0,0,0,,奇怪的联系\N{\fs15\}The weird connections,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.56,0:02:10.83,Default,,0,0,0,,创造我们的动力\N{\fs15\}the dynamic forces that created us.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.83,0:02:19.00,Default,,0,0,0,,一个拥有像你和我一样复杂大脑的物种\N{\fs15\}A species with a brain as complex as yours and mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.00,0:02:28.80,标题,,0,0,0,,{\move(320,260,320,220,0,1800)\fs50\fsp15\blur8\be1\fad(500,500)\c&H897364&}{\t(0,1800,0.5,\fs22\blur1\fsp5\c&HFFFFFF&)}被 点 亮 的 星 球
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.19,0:02:47.39,标题,,0,0,0,,{\fs38\pos(320,85)\fad(500,500)}觉 醒
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.99,0:02:48.93,Default,,0,0,0,,人脑是独一无二的\N{\fs15\}The human brain is unique.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.17,0:02:56.37,Default,,0,0,0,,不仅因为它的大小  而且因为它的能力\N{\fs15\}Not just because of its size, but also its ability.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.54,0:03:02.58,Default,,0,0,0,,它可以应对危险  苛刻的挑战\N{\fs15\}It can meet challenges that are dangerous, demanding.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.72,0:03:10.52,Default,,0,0,0,,史密斯：而且非常荒谬\N{\fs15\}SMITH: And wonderfully absurd.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.60,0:03:58.97,Default,,0,0,0,,史密斯：在西班牙  每年有数千人聚在一起\N{\fs15\}SMITH: In Spain, thousands come together every year
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.00,0:04:03.01,Default,,0,0,0,,用人体建造塔楼\N{\fs15\}to build towers out of people.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.99,0:04:25.79,Default,,0,0,0,,史密斯：一座十层楼高的人塔  上面有最年轻的孩子\N{\fs15\}SMITH: A ten-story human tower with the youngest kids on top.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.83,0:04:27.76,Default,,0,0,0,,是的\N{\fs15\}Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.80,0:04:30.97,Default,,0,0,0,,克劳迪娅和玛丽娜  他们七岁\N{\fs15\}Claudia and Marina, they're seven.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.62,0:07:05.12,Default,,0,0,0,,史密斯：人类和地球上其他生物都不一样\N{\fs15\}SMITH: Humans are like no other creature on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.15,0:07:09.63,Default,,0,0,0,,我们做的这些事情似乎毫无意义\N{\fs15\}We do these things that might seem pointless,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.66,0:07:13.96,Default,,0,0,0,,不是因为我们愚蠢  而是因为我们聪明\N{\fs15\}not because we're stupid; because we're smart.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.00,0:07:17.13,Default,,0,0,0,,我们一起工作\N{\fs15\}And we work as one.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.17,0:07:21.17,Default,,0,0,0,,是那种把我们的思想联系在一起的能力\N{\fs15\}It's that ability to link our minds together
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.20,0:07:23.97,Default,,0,0,0,,把那些女孩放在塔顶上\N{\fs15\}that put those girls on top of that tower
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.01,0:07:27.11,Default,,0,0,0,,把男人和女人放在太空中\N{\fs15\}and also put men and women up in space.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.85,0:07:33.82,Default,,0,0,0,,其中之一是莱兰·梅尔文\N{\fs15\}One of them is Leland Melvin.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.69,0:07:44.06,Default,,0,0,0,,前NFL球员  机械工程师和宇航员\N{\fs15\}Former NFL player, mechanical engineer, and astronaut.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:46.16,0:07:48.80,Default,,0,0,0,,坚强  聪明  勇敢\N{\fs15\}Strong, smart, brave,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.83,0:07:51.83,Default,,0,0,0,,而且几乎势不可挡\N{\fs15\}and pretty much unstoppable.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.87,0:07:56.64,Default,,0,0,0,,但利兰几乎没有飞到太空\N{\fs15\}But Leland nearly didn't make it to space.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.67,0:08:00.14,Default,,0,0,0,,训练中的一次意外使他的梦想停止了\N{\fs15\}An accident in his training brought his dreams to a halt.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.85,0:08:10.22,Default,,0,0,0,,梅尔文：真正模拟地球太空行走的唯一方法\N{\fs15\}MELVIN: The only way to really simulate a spacewalk on Earth
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.25,0:08:12.22,Default,,0,0,0,,在游泳池里\N{\fs15\}is in a pool.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.25,0:08:17.89,Default,,0,0,0,,我记得我穿上宇航服  戴上手套  穿上靴子\N{\fs15\}I remember getting in the suit, putting my gloves on, my boots.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.90,0:08:27.64,Default,,0,0,0,,梅尔文：当你穿着宇航服下潜的时候\N{\fs15\}MELVIN: As you're going down in the spacesuit,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.67,0:08:29.61,Default,,0,0,0,,你得清理耳朵\N{\fs15\}you have to clear your ears.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.18,0:08:36.14,Default,,0,0,0,,梅尔文：往下潜到十英尺\N{\fs15\}MELVIN: Ten feet down,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.18,0:08:38.88,Default,,0,0,0,,我意识到泡沫塑料块\N{\fs15\}I realized that the Styrofoam block,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.91,0:08:41.02,Default,,0,0,0,,堵住鼻子吹气来清空耳朵\N{\fs15\}you press your nose against it to clear your ears,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.05,0:08:43.82,Default,,0,0,0,,我的头盔不见了\N{\fs15\}was missing in my helmet.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.85,0:08:47.89,Default,,0,0,0,,我告诉测试主管  把耳机的音量调大\N{\fs15\}I tell the test director, turn the volume in the headset up.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.92,0:08:51.53,Default,,0,0,0,,我努力使压力均衡\N{\fs15\}I was straining to equalize the pressure.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.06,0:08:56.53,Default,,0,0,0,,然后  我立即听到除了静电以外什么都没有\N{\fs15\}And then, I immediately hear nothing but static.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.87,0:09:01.80,Default,,0,0,0,,他们把我从水里拖出来\N{\fs15\}They were pulling me out of the water.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.04,0:09:07.08,Default,,0,0,0,,当时我看到飞行外科医生朝我走来\N{\fs15\}And now I see the flight surgeon walking towards me.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.54,0:09:11.91,Default,,0,0,0,,他伸手摸我的右耳\N{\fs15\}He reaches up and touches my right ear.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.95,0:09:15.05,Default,,0,0,0,,他在动嘴唇  但我什么也没听到\N{\fs15\}He's moving his lips, but I don't hear anything he's saying.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.15,0:09:19.76,Default,,0,0,0,,然后我能感觉到血开始往下滴\N{\fs15\}And then I can feel the blood starting to trickle down
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.79,0:09:21.96,Default,,0,0,0,,在我脸的侧面\N{\fs15\}on the side of my face.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.99,0:09:25.96,Default,,0,0,0,,我想  哇！ 真的出了点问题\N{\fs15\}I'm like, 'Wow, something's really wrong.'
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.99,0:09:28.06,Default,,0,0,0,,我完全聋了\N{\fs15\}I was completely deaf.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.83,0:09:35.80,Default,,0,0,0,,我的大脑和耳朵之间的联系\N{\fs15\}Somehow the connection between my brain and my ears
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.84,0:09:38.74,Default,,0,0,0,,被切断了\N{\fs15\}had been severed,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.77,0:09:42.75,Default,,0,0,0,,以及我去太空的机会\N{\fs15\}along with my chances of going to space.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.78,0:09:48.78,Default,,0,0,0,,这次事故使我深表感激\N{\fs15\}The accident gave me a profound appreciation
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.82,0:09:52.66,Default,,0,0,0,,在我们认为理所当然的事情上\N{\fs15\}in what we take for granted.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.69,0:09:57.66,Default,,0,0,0,,使我们成为我们的东西：我们的大脑\N{\fs15\}The thing that makes us us: our brain.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.83,0:10:02.10,Default,,0,0,0,,人脑使我们与\N{\fs15\}The human brain sets us apart
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.13,0:10:07.10,Default,,0,0,0,,地球上所有其他生物都不同\N{\fs15\}from all other creatures on this planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.14,0:10:10.51,Default,,0,0,0,,它看起来像一块果冻\N{\fs15\}It might look like a lump of Jell-O,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.54,0:10:13.64,Default,,0,0,0,,但它是我们宇宙中最复杂的东西\N{\fs15\}but it's the most complex thing in our universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.81,0:10:20.85,Default,,0,0,0,,内部有一个拥有100万亿连接的庞大网络\N{\fs15\}Inside, there's a vast network with 100 trillion connections.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.95,0:10:28.62,Default,,0,0,0,,这比我们银河系中的恒星数量还要多\N{\fs15\}That's more than the number of stars in our own Milky Way.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.66,0:10:30.69,Default,,0,0,0,,它承载着我们的记忆\N{\fs15\}It hosts our memories.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.86,0:10:36.13,Default,,0,0,0,,我们的感觉\N{\fs15\}Our sensations.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.16,0:10:37.83,Default,,0,0,0,,我们的梦想\N{\fs15\}Our dreams.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.17,0:10:46.64,Default,,0,0,0,,所有这些都依赖于发射电信号的细胞\N{\fs15\}And all this depends on tiny cells firing electrical signals.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.68,0:10:50.78,Default,,0,0,0,,其中有860亿\N{\fs15\}There's 86 billion of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.81,0:10:54.15,Default,,0,0,0,,我们称之为神经元\N{\fs15\}We call them neurons.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.18,0:10:56.62,Default,,0,0,0,,史密斯：860亿\N{\fs15\}SMITH: 86 billion.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.65,0:10:57.82,Default,,0,0,0,,真的\N{\fs15\}Wow.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.85,0:11:00.49,Default,,0,0,0,,我很高兴有人在数\N{\fs15\}I'm just glad someone else was counting.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.52,0:11:04.46,Default,,0,0,0,,但问题是：\N{\fs15\}But here's the thing:
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.49,0:11:09.16,Default,,0,0,0,,地球上的大多数生命在没有大脑的情况下都很好\N{\fs15\}most of life on Earth does just fine without a brain.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.90,0:11:16.77,Default,,0,0,0,,我说的是地球上一些最古老的居民\N{\fs15\}I'm talking about some of Earth's oldest inhabitants.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.17,0:11:22.01,Default,,0,0,0,,有些无脑生物是如此成功\N{\fs15\}Some brainless creatures are so successful,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.04,0:11:25.81,Default,,0,0,0,,你甚至可以在太空中看到它们\N{\fs15\}you can even see them from space.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.85,0:11:26.92,Default,,0,0,0,,林格：在阳光明媚的日子\N{\fs15\}LINENGER: On a bright, sunny day,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.95,0:11:29.52,Default,,0,0,0,,我往下看了1000英里\N{\fs15\}I'm looking down, and for 1,000 miles,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.55,0:11:33.69,Default,,0,0,0,,我看到一个有组织的珊瑚城\N{\fs15\}I see an organized city of coral.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.56,0:11:43.50,Default,,0,0,0,,佩吉·惠特森：它们只是发光\N{\fs15\}PEGGY WHITSON: They just glow.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.53,0:11:46.80,Default,,0,0,0,,就像世界上最美的艺术一样\N{\fs15\}It's just like the most beautiful art in the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.14,0:11:53.74,Default,,0,0,0,,梅尔文：这一抹色彩\N{\fs15\}MELVIN: This burst of color.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.61,0:11:59.71,Default,,0,0,0,,我从未见过如此鲜艳的色彩\N{\fs15\}I'd never seen colors that vibrant before.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.75,0:12:04.59,Default,,0,0,0,,令人惊讶的是  珊瑚是巨大的  静止的结构\N{\fs15\}It's kind of amazing that corals are vast, motionless structures,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.62,0:12:06.99,Default,,0,0,0,,没有大脑就可以茁壮成长\N{\fs15\}that thrive without a brain.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.76,0:12:12.90,Default,,0,0,0,,史密斯：在这个无脑的国家\N{\fs15\}SMITH: In the country of the brainless,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.93,0:12:15.73,Default,,0,0,0,,小小脑袋就是国王\N{\fs15\}the tiny-brained is king.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.76,0:12:17.40,Default,,0,0,0,,见见这个小家伙\N{\fs15\}Meet this little guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.10,0:12:25.07,Default,,0,0,0,,他和我们的共同点比你想象的要多\N{\fs15\}He's got more in common with us than you might think.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.11,0:12:28.84,Default,,0,0,0,,在里面  他也有神经元  只是数量不多\N{\fs15\}Inside, he's got neurons, too, just not as many.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.95,0:12:32.75,Default,,0,0,0,,大约200\N{\fs15\}About 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.78,0:12:35.12,Default,,0,0,0,,有点像入门包\N{\fs15\}Kind of a starter kit.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.49,0:12:45.63,Default,,0,0,0,,他是一个寻找家的婴儿海鞘\N{\fs15\}He's a baby sea squirt looking for a home.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.66,0:12:47.60,Default,,0,0,0,,他的神经元做简单的事情\N{\fs15\}His neurons do simple stuff,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.63,0:12:51.03,Default,,0,0,0,,就像探测光线和抽动尾巴一样\N{\fs15\}like detect light and twitch his tail.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.50,0:12:53.97,Default,,0,0,0,,但问题是：\N{\fs15\}But here's the thing:
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.00,0:13:00.11,Default,,0,0,0,,一旦找到合适的石头  他的游泳日就结束了\N{\fs15\}once he's found the right rock, his swimming days are over.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.14,0:13:04.11,Default,,0,0,0,,在他的余生里  他一直呆在原地\N{\fs15\}For the rest of his life, he stays put.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.15,0:13:09.78,Default,,0,0,0,,他甩下尾巴  消化使它移动的神经元\N{\fs15\}He dumps the tail and consumes the neurons that made it move.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.82,0:13:14.12,Default,,0,0,0,,然后  它成长为一个巨大的  古老的海鞘\N{\fs15\}Then, it grows into a big, old sea squirt.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.16,0:13:19.63,Default,,0,0,0,,将  使用或丢失  提升到一个全新的水平\N{\fs15\}Takes 'use it or lose it' to a whole new level.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.66,0:13:21.00,Default,,0,0,0,,梅尔文：你知道  这是一种奇怪的想法\N{\fs15\}MELVIN: It's kind of a freaky thought that, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.03,0:13:25.53,Default,,0,0,0,,当神经元发育时  它们不是用来思考的\N{\fs15\}when neurons were developed, they weren't for thinking.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.57,0:13:28.80,Default,,0,0,0,,它们是为了简单的运动\N{\fs15\}They were for simple motion or movement.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.84,0:13:33.81,Default,,0,0,0,,但是有一天  像这样的神经元  我们大脑中的神经元\N{\fs15\}But one day, neurons like those, the ones inside our brains,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.84,0:13:34.84,Default,,0,0,0,,有助于创造事物\N{\fs15\}would help create things
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.88,0:13:38.48,Default,,0,0,0,,就像火箭飞船进入太空一样\N{\fs15\}like rocket ships going to space,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.51,0:13:40.98,Default,,0,0,0,,城市和音乐\N{\fs15\}cities and music.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.85,0:13:49.79,Default,,0,0,0,,史密斯：抽动尾巴移动一两码\N{\fs15\}SMITH: Making a tail twitch to move a yard or two
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.82,0:13:52.53,Default,,0,0,0,,只需要几个神经元\N{\fs15\}requires just a few neurons.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.56,0:13:54.80,Default,,0,0,0,,但是  更先进的东西\N{\fs15\}However, the more advanced stuff,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.83,0:13:58.53,Default,,0,0,0,,这需要更多的东西\N{\fs15\}that needs an awful lot more.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.57,0:14:01.64,Default,,0,0,0,,生物需要感知周围的环境\N{\fs15\}Life needs to sense its surroundings,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.67,0:14:05.37,Default,,0,0,0,,否则  它只是在黑暗中挣扎\N{\fs15\}otherwise, it's just flailing around in the dark.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.95,0:14:20.16,Default,,0,0,0,,史密斯：没有什么比人脑更复杂的了\N{\fs15\}SMITH: There is nothing more complex than the human brain.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.19,0:14:23.09,Default,,0,0,0,,但更复杂的是\N{\fs15\}But the more complicated something is,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.13,0:14:25.73,Default,,0,0,0,,越是可能出错\N{\fs15\}the more ways it can go wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.76,0:14:26.73,Default,,0,0,0,,（鸟叫声）\N{\fs15\}(bird shrieks)
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.76,0:14:30.73,Default,,0,0,0,,梅尔文：在我的训练事故之后\N{\fs15\}MELVIN: After my training accident,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.77,0:14:34.60,Default,,0,0,0,,医生们不知道我出了什么问题\N{\fs15\}the doctors couldn't figure out what was wrong with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.64,0:14:37.84,Default,,0,0,0,,一切看起来都完好无损\N{\fs15\}Everything looked physically intact,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.87,0:14:40.18,Default,,0,0,0,,但他们不能治好我\N{\fs15\}but they couldn't fix me.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.21,0:14:43.75,Default,,0,0,0,,我完全聋了\N{\fs15\}I was completely deaf.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.78,0:14:48.12,Default,,0,0,0,,我进入太空的目标似乎被挫败了\N{\fs15\}My goal of getting to space seemed to be thwarted.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.15,0:14:49.72,Default,,0,0,0,,但我能想到的只是\N{\fs15\}But all I could think about
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.75,0:14:53.72,Default,,0,0,0,,我是否曾听过我再次演奏的音乐\N{\fs15\}was whether I'd ever hear music that I played again.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.76,0:14:56.89,Default,,0,0,0,,音乐一直是我生物的重要组成部分\N{\fs15\}Music has been such a big part of my life.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.93,0:14:59.89,Default,,0,0,0,,（弹钢琴）\N{\fs15\}(playing piano)
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.93,0:15:03.00,Default,,0,0,0,,所以  当音乐安静的时候…\N{\fs15\}And so, when the music was silent...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.60,0:15:10.44,Default,,0,0,0,,就在那时  我崩溃了  开始哭泣\N{\fs15\}That's when I just broke down and started crying.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.64,0:15:15.94,Default,,0,0,0,,史密斯：利兰的耳朵很好\N{\fs15\}SMITH: Leland's ears were fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.98,0:15:17.81,Default,,0,0,0,,这不是问题所在\N{\fs15\}That's not where the problem was.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.85,0:15:20.95,Default,,0,0,0,,因为你不只是用耳朵听\N{\fs15\}Because you don't just hear with your ears,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.98,0:15:23.79,Default,,0,0,0,,你的大脑也能听到\N{\fs15\}you also hear with your brain.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.82,0:15:26.79,Default,,0,0,0,,所有感官都一样\N{\fs15\}It's the same for all the senses,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.82,0:15:30.96,Default,,0,0,0,,他们把我们的大脑与外界联系起来\N{\fs15\}they link our brains to the outside world.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.99,0:15:35.93,Default,,0,0,0,,数百代人的进化都是为了适应这个世界\N{\fs15\}And over hundreds of generations they evolve to suit that world,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.96,0:15:38.60,Default,,0,0,0,,不管有多严厉\N{\fs15\}no matter how harsh it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.49,0:16:08.73,Default,,0,0,0,,史密斯：猎人在这里已经住了几千年了\N{\fs15\}SMITH: Hunters have lived here for thousands of years.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.97,0:16:17.11,Default,,0,0,0,,但为了生存  他们借用了生物的感官\N{\fs15\}But to survive, they borrow the senses of a creature
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.14,0:16:19.84,Default,,0,0,0,,在这里呆得更久了\N{\fs15\}that's been here even longer.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.84,0:18:02.78,Default,,0,0,0,,史密斯：老鹰就像一个武器望远镜\N{\fs15\}SMITH: The eagle is like a weaponized telescope.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.81,0:18:06.71,Default,,0,0,0,,它能看见两英里外的狐狸\N{\fs15\}It can see a fox up to two miles away.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.75,0:18:12.62,Default,,0,0,0,,在这里  这是为生存而战的关键工具\N{\fs15\}Out here, that's a crucial tool in the fight for survival.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.58,0:19:14.78,Default,,0,0,0,,史密斯：但是像鹰一样看东西\N{\fs15\}SMITH: But to see like an eagle,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.82,0:19:17.79,Default,,0,0,0,,你需要的不仅仅是鹰眼\N{\fs15\}you need more than eagle eyes;
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.82,0:19:20.02,Default,,0,0,0,,你需要一个鹰脑\N{\fs15\}you need an eagle brain.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.99,0:19:28.20,Default,,0,0,0,,梅尔文：眼睛传递着我们周围世界的大量数据\N{\fs15\}MELVIN: Eyes deliver masses of data about the world around us,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.23,0:19:30.80,Default,,0,0,0,,以及所有拯救生命的数据\N{\fs15\}and all that lifesaving data
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.83,0:19:35.04,Default,,0,0,0,,需要一些强有力的东西来理解它\N{\fs15\}needed something powerful to make sense of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.07,0:19:38.54,Default,,0,0,0,,简单地说  如果你是有眼睛的动物\N{\fs15\}Simply put, if you're an animal with eyes,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.57,0:19:43.04,Default,,0,0,0,,你需要比海鞘更大的大脑\N{\fs15\}you're gonna need a bigger brain than a sea squirt.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.08,0:19:45.71,Default,,0,0,0,,眼睛是真正的游戏改变者\N{\fs15\}Eyes were a real game changer.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.02,0:19:50.69,Default,,0,0,0,,但不仅仅是眼睛\N{\fs15\}But it's not just the eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.75,0:19:55.99,Default,,0,0,0,,生物必须发展出一系列的感官\N{\fs15\}Creatures had to develop an array of senses
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.02,0:19:58.16,Default,,0,0,0,,每一个都经过校准处理\N{\fs15\}that are each calibrated to deal
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.19,0:20:01.86,Default,,0,0,0,,随着地球环境的不断变化\N{\fs15\}with the ever-changing environment of Planet Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.97,0:20:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,不仅仅是不新鲜的甜点\N{\fs15\}Not just barren desserts,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.03,0:20:08.70,Default,,0,0,0,,但是这些茂密的丛林\N{\fs15\}but these very dense jungles,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.74,0:20:12.01,Default,,0,0,0,,丰富的海洋礁\N{\fs15\}teeming ocean reefs,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.04,0:20:14.64,Default,,0,0,0,,甚至是冰冷的北极垃圾\N{\fs15\}and even icy Arctic waste.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.48,0:20:20.08,Default,,0,0,0,,地球上各种各样的景观发挥了重要作用\N{\fs15\}The planet's varied landscapes played a significant role
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.11,0:20:22.65,Default,,0,0,0,,动物的感觉\N{\fs15\}in how animals sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.75,0:20:30.12,Default,,0,0,0,,史密斯：他们怎么办  我们怎么办\N{\fs15\}SMITH: What goes for them, goes for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.16,0:20:33.73,Default,,0,0,0,,这颗行星也塑造了我们的感官\N{\fs15\}The planet shaped our senses, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.73,0:20:38.43,Default,,0,0,0,,你可能没注意到\N{\fs15\}It's something you might not notice
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.47,0:20:40.57,Default,,0,0,0,,除非你离开这个星球\N{\fs15\}unless you leave the planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.61,0:20:46.14,Default,,0,0,0,,麦克·马西米诺：我们的感官已经进化了\N{\fs15\}MIKE MASSIMINO: Our senses have evolved
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.17,0:20:49.98,Default,,0,0,0,,来适应地球\N{\fs15\}to operate on Planet Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.01,0:20:51.81,Default,,0,0,0,,梅杰米森：当你在太空时\N{\fs15\}MAE JEMISON: When you're up in space,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.85,0:20:54.95,Default,,0,0,0,,内耳没有上下运动\N{\fs15\}the inner ear isn't registering an up and down.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.69,0:20:59.82,Default,,0,0,0,,梅尔文：所以  你的方向感\N{\fs15\}MELVIN: So, your sense of orientation
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.85,0:21:01.69,Default,,0,0,0,,只来自你的眼睛\N{\fs15\}only comes from your eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.69,0:21:04.66,Default,,0,0,0,,马西米诺：你知道那种奇怪的感觉\N{\fs15\}MASSIMINO: You know that weird feeling
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.69,0:21:05.83,Default,,0,0,0,,在你的胃深处\N{\fs15\}in the pit of your stomach,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.86,0:21:08.63,Default,,0,0,0,,好像你越过过山车的顶部时\N{\fs15\}when you go over the top of a rollercoaster?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.83,0:21:13.54,Default,,0,0,0,,基本上在那种感觉持续了一整天\N{\fs15\}I was basically in that moment for an entire day.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.17,0:21:17.84,Default,,0,0,0,,斯托特：我们是地球人\N{\fs15\}STOTT: We're Earthlings.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.87,0:21:21.11,Default,,0,0,0,,我们就是这样\N{\fs15\}That's just who we are.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.14,0:21:23.95,Default,,0,0,0,,梅尔文：原始大脑感官的进化\N{\fs15\}MELVIN: The evolution of the senses in the primitive brain
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.98,0:21:27.82,Default,,0,0,0,,允许生物与我们的星球互动\N{\fs15\}have allowed living creatures to interact with our planet
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.85,0:21:29.98,Default,,0,0,0,,以前所未有的方式\N{\fs15\}in a way like never before.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.02,0:21:31.95,Default,,0,0,0,,但是从太空看我们的星球\N{\fs15\}But looking at our planet from space,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.99,0:21:37.96,Default,,0,0,0,,你可以看到它不仅仅是变化的  它是动态的\N{\fs15\}you can see it's not just varied, it's dynamic.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.00,0:21:47.00,Default,,0,0,0,,史密斯：有时候  环境变化很快\N{\fs15\}SMITH: Sometimes, the environment changes quickly,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.03,0:21:51.51,Default,,0,0,0,,当这种情况发生时  你必须尽快适应\N{\fs15\}and when that happens, you have to be just as fast to adapt.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.54,0:21:54.61,Default,,0,0,0,,就像海平面毫无预警地上升\N{\fs15\}Like when the sea level rises without warning,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.64,0:21:58.11,Default,,0,0,0,,现在  你是一个孤岛的弃儿\N{\fs15\}and now, you're an island castaway.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.93,0:22:13.90,Default,,0,0,0,,猕猴的手非常棒\N{\fs15\}Macaques are great with their hands.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.93,0:22:18.67,Default,,0,0,0,,他们剥水果  爬树  做彼此的头发\N{\fs15\}They peel fruit, climb trees, and do each other's hair.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.17,0:22:26.04,Default,,0,0,0,,但在这些岛屿上  它们所做的事情是其他猕猴所不具备的\N{\fs15\}But on these islands, they do something no other macaques do.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.98,0:23:11.82,Default,,0,0,0,,他们用石头作为剥牡蛎壳的工具\N{\fs15\}They use rocks as tools to shuck oysters.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.49,0:23:16.72,Default,,0,0,0,,猕猴通常不吃它们\N{\fs15\}Macaques don't normally eat them,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.76,0:23:19.63,Default,,0,0,0,,但当他们被上涨的海水搁浅时\N{\fs15\}but when they were stranded by the rising sea,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.66,0:23:22.66,Default,,0,0,0,,他们需要新的吃饭方式\N{\fs15\}they needed new ways to get a meal.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.97,0:23:26.97,Default,,0,0,0,,他们不是天生就具备这种技能的\N{\fs15\}They weren't born with this skill;
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.00,0:23:30.07,Default,,0,0,0,,一只聪明的猴子必须解决这个问题\N{\fs15\}a smart monkey had to work it out.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.75,0:23:41.45,Default,,0,0,0,,这是只有复杂的大脑才能做到的  --\N{\fs15\}This is something only complex brains can do--
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.48,0:23:43.95,Default,,0,0,0,,不仅仅是感觉和反应\N{\fs15\}not just sense and react,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.99,0:23:46.62,Default,,0,0,0,,但学习\N{\fs15\}but learn,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.65,0:23:49.66,Default,,0,0,0,,适应并解决问题\N{\fs15\}adapt and problem solve.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.13,0:23:57.80,Default,,0,0,0,,但仅仅因为猕猴能学会剥牡蛎皮\N{\fs15\}But just because a macaque can learn to shuck oysters
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.83,0:24:01.34,Default,,0,0,0,,并不意味着它会开一家海鲜餐馆\N{\fs15\}doesn't mean it's gonna open a seafood restaurant.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.67,0:24:06.74,Default,,0,0,0,,只有人类才能做出这种精神上的飞跃\N{\fs15\}Only a human would make that mental leap.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.77,0:24:09.51,Default,,0,0,0,,那么  我们为什么会如此不同呢\N{\fs15\}So, how come we're so different?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.85,0:24:23.79,Default,,0,0,0,,史密斯：猴子是太空中第一批灵长类动物\N{\fs15\}SMITH: Monkeys were the first primates in space,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.83,0:24:27.63,Default,,0,0,0,,但这不是他们的主意\N{\fs15\}but it wasn't exactly their idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.66,0:24:30.16,Default,,0,0,0,,事实上  他们可能反对\N{\fs15\}In fact, they were probably against it.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.20,0:24:34.14,Default,,0,0,0,,那么  为什么我们是有着伟大想法的猿类\N{\fs15\}So, how come we're the apes with the big ideas?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:34.17,0:24:37.87,Default,,0,0,0,,好吧  说来话长\N{\fs15\}Well, it's a long story.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.91,0:24:40.64,Default,,0,0,0,,关于可能不存在的事物的故事\N{\fs15\}A story about something that may not exist
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.68,0:24:43.81,Default,,0,0,0,,太阳系的其他地方\N{\fs15\}anywhere else in the solar system,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.85,0:24:45.58,Default,,0,0,0,,也许是宇宙\N{\fs15\}maybe the universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:48.85,0:24:51.49,Default,,0,0,0,,火\N{\fs15\}Fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:03.82,0:25:05.62,Default,,0,0,0,,我是酋长夫人
Dialogue: 0,0:25:06.66,0:25:08.46,Default,,0,0,0,,负责管理圣火
Dialogue: 0,0:25:20.01,0:25:23.41,Default,,0,0,0,,这个火是我们和先祖的直接纽带
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.51,0:25:26.51,Default,,0,0,0,,如果火熄灭了
Dialogue: 0,0:25:27.22,0:25:30.12,Default,,0,0,0,,我们和先祖就会永远失去联系
Dialogue: 0,0:25:31.69,0:25:35.60,Default,,0,0,0,,史密斯：希姆巴人一直在燃烧着同一团火\N{\fs15\}SMITH: The Himba people have kept this same fire burning
Dialogue: 0,0:25:35.63,0:25:37.70,Default,,0,0,0,,世世代代\N{\fs15\}for generations.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:42.06,0:25:45.56,Default,,0,0,0,,我们拿柴灰来编辫子
Dialogue: 0,0:25:49.37,0:25:50.87,Default,,0,0,0,,有了火
Dialogue: 0,0:25:50.87,0:25:52.87,Default,,0,0,0,,我们可以加热石头和植物
Dialogue: 0,0:25:55.03,0:25:58.03,Default,,0,0,0,,制造烟雾用来熏香
Dialogue: 0,0:26:00.08,0:26:03.08,Default,,0,0,0,,火是我们生存的必需品
Dialogue: 0,0:26:26.58,0:26:28.98,Default,,0,0,0,,我们吃的所有东西都是用火烹饪
Dialogue: 0,0:26:32.97,0:26:34.97,Default,,0,0,0,,我们把肉放入大火中
Dialogue: 0,0:26:39.07,0:26:40.07,Default,,0,0,0,,我们才能很好地烹制
Dialogue: 0,0:26:40.37,0:26:41.77,Default,,0,0,0,,食物才好吃
Dialogue: 0,0:26:05.79,0:26:09.76,Default,,0,0,0,,史密斯：据我们所知  这颗行星是唯一的\N{\fs15\}SMITH: As far as we know, this planet is the only one
Dialogue: 0,0:26:09.80,0:26:14.60,Default,,0,0,0,,有适当的燃烧条件\N{\fs15\}with the right conditions for fire to burn.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:14.64,0:26:19.74,Default,,0,0,0,,但有一件事是火给了我们最重要的\N{\fs15\}But there's one thing that fire gives us above all else.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:45.00,0:26:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,,史密斯：但是烹调食物有好处\N{\fs15\}SMITH: But cooking food does something
Dialogue: 0,0:26:48.04,0:26:53.78,Default,,0,0,0,,这比让它可口更重要\N{\fs15\}that's way more important than just making it tasty.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:53.81,0:26:58.48,Default,,0,0,0,,梅尔文：哇  我们有火了  准备好吃饭了吗\N{\fs15\}MELVIN: Woo! We got fire, are we ready for food?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:58.51,0:27:03.85,Default,,0,0,0,,作为人类  我们有着这些渴望力量的大脑\N{\fs15\}We as humans have these power-hungry brains.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.89,0:27:06.09,Default,,0,0,0,,我们身体的一大块能量\N{\fs15\}A big chunk of our body's energy
Dialogue: 0,0:27:06.12,0:27:08.52,Default,,0,0,0,,必须用来让它们保持运转\N{\fs15\}has to be used to keep them running.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:08.56,0:27:10.19,Default,,0,0,0,,来 宝贝  翻个身\N{\fs15\}Turn, baby, turn.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:10.22,0:27:12.86,Default,,0,0,0,,通过烹饪  我们实际上正在\N{\fs15\}By cooking, we're actually breaking down
Dialogue: 0,0:27:12.89,0:27:15.53,Default,,0,0,0,,破坏食物的细胞壁\N{\fs15\}the cell walls of the food
Dialogue: 0,0:27:15.56,0:27:18.97,Default,,0,0,0,,因而释放出更多的营养和卡路里\N{\fs15\}that releases so many more nutrients and calories,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:19.00,0:27:20.80,Default,,0,0,0,,为我们的大脑加满油\N{\fs15\}to help fuel our big brains.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:24.57,0:27:27.14,Default,,0,0,0,,我们物种历史上的一个关键时刻\N{\fs15\}One of the key moments in the history of our species
Dialogue: 0,0:27:27.17,0:27:30.81,Default,,0,0,0,,是我们的祖先用火的时候\N{\fs15\}was when our ancestors harnessed fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:30.85,0:27:32.81,Default,,0,0,0,,好吧  把盘子拿来\N{\fs15\}Alright, get your plates.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:32.85,0:27:36.52,Default,,0,0,0,,理论认为  烹饪让我们获得更多的能量\N{\fs15\}The theory goes, cooking let us get more energy
Dialogue: 0,0:27:36.55,0:27:38.99,Default,,0,0,0,,从每一口食物中\N{\fs15\}out of every bite of food.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:39.02,0:27:42.56,Default,,0,0,0,,所以我们用更少的时间来喂养我们的大脑\N{\fs15\}So we spent less time feeding our brain
Dialogue: 0,0:27:42.59,0:27:44.86,Default,,0,0,0,,还有更多的时间使用它\N{\fs15\}and more time using it.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:48.90,0:27:54.14,Default,,0,0,0,,史密斯：试着去一个不受火影响的日子\N{\fs15\}SMITH: Try going a day that isn't touched by fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:54.17,0:27:57.81,Default,,0,0,0,,你无法想象没有它的生物\N{\fs15\}You couldn't imagine life without it.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:57.84,0:27:59.87,Default,,0,0,0,,但是一个可以控制火焰的大脑\N{\fs15\}But a brain that could harness fire
Dialogue: 0,0:27:59.91,0:28:01.74,Default,,0,0,0,,可能一开始就没有进化\N{\fs15\}may not have evolved in the first place
Dialogue: 0,0:28:01.78,0:28:07.08,Default,,0,0,0,,如果不是因为这么强大的力量\N{\fs15\}if it wasn't for a force so powerful,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:07.11,0:28:10.35,Default,,0,0,0,,它是地球上最高的山脉\N{\fs15\}it made the highest mountains on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:46.61,0:29:49.08,Default,,0,0,0,,史密斯：化石告诉我们这些山\N{\fs15\}SMITH: The fossils tell us that these mountains,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:49.12,0:29:53.96,Default,,0,0,0,,曾经在海底  现金被推到了高空\N{\fs15\}once at the bottom of the sea, were forced high into the sky.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:57.99,0:29:58.96,Default,,0,0,0,,当你在轨道上时\N{\fs15\}LINENGER: When you're in orbit,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:58.99,0:30:01.80,Default,,0,0,0,,当你经过喜马拉雅山时\N{\fs15\}as you come over the Himalaya Mountains,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:01.83,0:30:05.97,Default,,0,0,0,,你几乎觉得你需要启动一点推进器\N{\fs15\}you almost feel like you need to fire the thrusters a little bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:06.00,0:30:08.14,Default,,0,0,0,,你可以知道次大陆在哪里\N{\fs15\}You can tell where that subcontinent
Dialogue: 0,0:30:08.17,0:30:10.80,Default,,0,0,0,,刚刚挤进亚洲大陆\N{\fs15\}just jammed into the Asian continent
Dialogue: 0,0:30:10.84,0:30:14.04,Default,,0,0,0,,把那些山推倒\N{\fs15\}and thrust those mountains up.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:14.08,0:30:17.01,Default,,0,0,0,,克里斯·哈德菲尔德：平滑平坦度之间的碰撞\N{\fs15\}CHRIS HADFIELD: This collision between the smooth flatness
Dialogue: 0,0:30:17.04,0:30:20.81,Default,,0,0,0,,关于印度和这些崎岖  褶皱的山脉\N{\fs15\}of India and these rugged, crumpled mountains,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:20.85,0:30:24.42,Default,,0,0,0,,就像看着一辆超慢速的火车残骸\N{\fs15\}it's like watching a super slow-motion train wreck.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:26.72,0:30:28.49,Default,,0,0,0,,马西米诺：离得越远\N{\fs15\}MASSIMINO: The further you get away,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:28.52,0:30:30.82,Default,,0,0,0,,你可以看到这些主要的主题\N{\fs15\}you can kind of see these overarching themes
Dialogue: 0,0:30:30.86,0:30:32.89,Default,,0,0,0,,我们星球的形成方式\N{\fs15\}to the way our planet is formed.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:38.67,0:30:40.97,Default,,0,0,0,,梅尔文：正是这些力量会改变\N{\fs15\}MELVIN: It was forces like these that would transform
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.00,0:30:43.14,Default,,0,0,0,,我们岩石的一个特定角落\N{\fs15\}one particular corner of our rock
Dialogue: 0,0:30:43.17,0:30:46.11,Default,,0,0,0,,进入人类的摇篮\N{\fs15\}into the cradle of humanity.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:50.01,0:30:53.05,Default,,0,0,0,,东非大裂谷\N{\fs15\}The Great Rift Valley in East Africa
Dialogue: 0,0:30:53.08,0:30:58.72,Default,,0,0,0,,曾经是一片郁郁葱葱的绿色森林  是猿类的天堂\N{\fs15\}was once a lush green forest, a paradise for apes.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:06.86,0:31:10.56,Default,,0,0,0,,但是地壳移动  山脉上升\N{\fs15\}But the Earth's crust shifted, mountains rose,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:10.60,0:31:14.94,Default,,0,0,0,,气候也发生了变化  使得这里的生物变得更加艰难\N{\fs15\}and the climate changed, making it a much tougher place to live.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:20.64,0:31:24.71,Default,,0,0,0,,很难确切知道我们的祖先是如何适应的\N{\fs15\}It's hard to really know exactly how our ancestors adapted
Dialogue: 0,0:31:24.75,0:31:26.88,Default,,0,0,0,,数百万年来\N{\fs15\}over millions of years.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:29.82,0:31:31.85,Default,,0,0,0,,这些变化可能促使类人猿做事\N{\fs15\}The changes may have pushed apes to do things
Dialogue: 0,0:31:31.89,0:31:34.82,Default,,0,0,0,,比如创新工具\N{\fs15\}like innovate the tools.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:36.96,0:31:39.49,Default,,0,0,0,,或者双腿行走\N{\fs15\}Or walk on two legs.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:41.73,0:31:44.77,Default,,0,0,0,,甚至可以利用火势\N{\fs15\}And even harness fire.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:44.80,0:31:49.97,Default,,0,0,0,,不管是什么  我们都是早期人类\N{\fs15\}Whatever it was, we came out the other side as early humans,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:50.00,0:31:51.67,Default,,0,0,0,,有更大的头脑\N{\fs15\}with bigger brains.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:54.78,0:31:57.08,Default,,0,0,0,,史密斯：我们在地球上实现了飞跃\N{\fs15\}SMITH: We took off across the planet,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:57.11,0:32:02.65,Default,,0,0,0,,我们带来了一种独特的人类技能\N{\fs15\}and there was one uniquely human skill we brought with us.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:02.68,0:32:05.55,Default,,0,0,0,,我在这儿  跟你说话\N{\fs15\}Here I am, talking to you,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:05.59,0:32:09.49,Default,,0,0,0,,你们中的一些人甚至在听\N{\fs15\}and some of you are even listening.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:09.52,0:32:12.79,Default,,0,0,0,,你听到的可能是最强大的工具\N{\fs15\}What you're hearing is probably the most powerful tool
Dialogue: 0,0:32:12.83,0:32:15.13,Default,,0,0,0,,我们已经掌握了\N{\fs15\}we've ever mastered.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:15.16,0:32:18.97,Default,,0,0,0,,那么  你怎么能有一个能讲一个好故事的大脑呢？\N{\fs15\}So, how do you get a brain that can tell a damn good story?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:32.85,0:32:34.65,Default,,0,0,0,,史密斯：我们说话\N{\fs15\}SMITH: We speak.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:41.02,0:32:45.46,Default,,0,0,0,,史密斯：我们把符号和声音与思想和事物联系起来\N{\fs15\}SMITH: We link signs and sounds to thoughts and things,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.49,0:32:49.80,Default,,0,0,0,,以无数的方式  创造出几乎无限的意义\N{\fs15\}in countless ways, creating almost infinite meanings.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:49.83,0:32:53.83,Default,,0,0,0,,这需要很大的脑力\N{\fs15\}That takes a lot of brain power.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:07.51,0:33:10.85,Default,,0,0,0,,朱莉Masaki：搬到香港真是太神奇了\N{\fs15\}JULIE MISAKI: Moving to Hong Kong has been amazing.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:13.89,0:33:15.86,Default,,0,0,0,,我来自日本\N{\fs15\}I'm originally from Japan,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:15.89,0:33:19.09,Default,,0,0,0,,但是我在香港已经住了六年了\N{\fs15\}but I've lived in Hong Kong for six years now.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:23.93,0:33:26.90,Default,,0,0,0,,但它也有挑战\N{\fs15\}But it has its challenges.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:28.94,0:33:32.01,Default,,0,0,0,,即使只是买晚餐也会变得复杂\N{\fs15\}Even just buying dinner can get complicated.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:35.54,0:33:38.68,Default,,0,0,0,,我们很多外国人都想学汉语\N{\fs15\}A lot of us foreigners try to learn Chinese,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:38.71,0:33:41.58,Default,,0,0,0,,但这并不总是容易的\N{\fs15\}but it's not always easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:43.52,0:33:47.05,Default,,0,0,0,,一个词实际上可以有多种含义\N{\fs15\}One word can actually have many meanings,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:47.09,0:33:49.52,Default,,0,0,0,,取决于你使用的音调\N{\fs15\}depending on the tone you use.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:51.06,0:33:57.66,Default,,0,0,0,,比如说  如果我说  肖    意思是  烧\N{\fs15\}For example, if I say xiao, it means burn,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:57.70,0:34:01.87,Default,,0,0,0,,或者小  意思很小\N{\fs15\}or xiao, it means little,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:01.90,0:34:05.61,Default,,0,0,0,,或者小笑  意思是笑\N{\fs15\}or xiao, it means laugh.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:09.48,0:34:14.78,Default,,0,0,0,,用错误的语调  你可能会遇到大麻烦\N{\fs15\}Use the wrong tone, you could be in big trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:14.82,0:34:16.58,Default,,0,0,0,,梅尔文：只有我们人类\N{\fs15\}MELVIN: It's only us human beings
Dialogue: 0,0:34:16.62,0:34:19.95,Default,,0,0,0,,已经发展出复杂的语言\N{\fs15\}that have developed complex language.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:19.99,0:34:22.12,Default,,0,0,0,,与其他语言不同\N{\fs15\}Unlike many other languages,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:22.16,0:34:25.13,Default,,0,0,0,,中国人使用大脑的音乐区域\N{\fs15\}Chinese uses the musical areas of the brain
Dialogue: 0,0:34:25.16,0:34:29.80,Default,,0,0,0,,从所有这些音调中提取意义\N{\fs15\}to extract meaning from all those tones.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:29.83,0:34:34.47,Default,,0,0,0,,这需要很大的处理能力\N{\fs15\}And that takes a lot of processing power.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:34.50,0:34:37.77,Default,,0,0,0,,但真正重要的问题是\N{\fs15\}But the really big question is
Dialogue: 0,0:34:37.80,0:34:42.94,Default,,0,0,0,,为什么我们有任何语言\N{\fs15\}why we have any language at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:42.98,0:34:46.68,Default,,0,0,0,,部分原因是我们的大脑很大\N{\fs15\}It's partly due to the size of our big brains.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:50.48,0:34:54.89,Default,,0,0,0,,但可能还有另一个因素在起作用\N{\fs15\}But there could be another factor at play.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:54.92,0:35:00.06,Default,,0,0,0,,一种理论是  它是非常微小的东西\N{\fs15\}One theory is that it was something really tiny.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:00.09,0:35:04.10,Default,,0,0,0,,有一种叫做foxp2的基因\N{\fs15\}There's a version of a gene, called FOXP2,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:04.13,0:35:07.00,Default,,0,0,0,,只有我们人类拥有\N{\fs15\}that only us humans have.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:07.03,0:35:10.54,Default,,0,0,0,,把它拿走  你就很难说话了\N{\fs15\}Take it away, and you'll struggle to talk.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:12.17,0:35:15.64,Default,,0,0,0,,没人知道我们是怎么产生这种变异的\N{\fs15\}No one knows how we've got this mutation.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:20.88,0:35:22.68,Default,,0,0,0,,但我们知道…\N{\fs15\}But we do know...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:25.19,0:35:27.69,Default,,0,0,0,,…它给了我们更精确的控制\N{\fs15\}...it gave us more precise control
Dialogue: 0,0:35:27.72,0:35:31.99,Default,,0,0,0,,通过我们的嘴和舌头肌肉\N{\fs15\}over our mouth and our tongue muscles.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:32.03,0:35:36.83,Default,,0,0,0,,让我们发出更复杂的声音\N{\fs15\}And that let us make more sophisticated sounds,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:36.86,0:35:39.83,Default,,0,0,0,,帮助我们把思想变成文字\N{\fs15\}helping us turn thoughts into words.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:44.00,0:35:46.54,Default,,0,0,0,,史密斯：小的基因突变使我们\N{\fs15\}SMITH: Small genetic twists turned us
Dialogue: 0,0:35:46.57,0:35:48.81,Default,,0,0,0,,一群咕噜咕噜的人\N{\fs15\}from a bunch of folks who grunt
Dialogue: 0,0:35:48.84,0:35:53.48,Default,,0,0,0,,对于一个能分辨晓和晓的物种来说\N{\fs15\}to a species that can tell xiao from xiao,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:53.51,0:35:55.98,Default,,0,0,0,,来自"xiao"\N{\fs15\}from xiao.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:56.02,0:36:00.15,Default,,0,0,0,,分享想法  交流想法\N{\fs15\}Sharing ideas, communicating them,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:00.19,0:36:05.56,Default,,0,0,0,,让我们做那些不可能的事情\N{\fs15\}lets us do things that alone would be impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:05.59,0:36:09.23,Default,,0,0,0,,这是开拓者所熟知的\N{\fs15\}Something pioneers know full well.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:18.84,0:36:21.07,Default,,0,0,0,,洛基·罗宾逊：好吧  我们开始吧\N{\fs15\}ROCKY ROBINSON: Okay, let's do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:21.11,0:36:22.74,Default,,0,0,0,,我得到了各种——我把它擦掉了\N{\fs15\}I'm getting all kinds-- I've wiped it off,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:22.78,0:36:24.91,Default,,0,0,0,,但是我身上有各种各样的盐\N{\fs15\}but I have all kinds of salt on me.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:24.95,0:36:26.75,Default,,0,0,0,,我的盾牌被盐覆盖了\N{\fs15\}My shield got covered in salt.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:26.78,0:36:29.38,Default,,0,0,0,,男：把水泵关掉\N{\fs15\}MAN: Turn the water pump off.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:29.42,0:36:30.75,Default,,0,0,0,,罗宾逊：我们在玻利维亚\N{\fs15\}ROBINSON: We're here in Bolivia
Dialogue: 0,0:36:30.78,0:36:35.16,Default,,0,0,0,,试图打破摩托车世界陆地速度纪录\N{\fs15\}trying to break the motorcycle world land speed record.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:35.19,0:36:36.76,Default,,0,0,0,,我们可能没有更好的机会\N{\fs15\}We probably don't have a better opportunity
Dialogue: 0,0:36:36.79,0:36:40.89,Default,,0,0,0,,比我们现在看到的还要快\N{\fs15\}than we have right now to see just how fast this bike will go.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:48.64,0:36:51.10,Default,,0,0,0,,这是一个巨大的团队努力\N{\fs15\}This is a huge team effort.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:51.14,0:36:54.54,Default,,0,0,0,,我们交流很多  团队和我\N{\fs15\}We communicate a lot, the team and I.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:54.58,0:36:56.94,Default,,0,0,0,,沟通是一个巨大的优势\N{\fs15\}Communication is a huge advantage.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:59.88,0:37:01.11,Default,,0,0,0,,需要这么多人\N{\fs15\}It takes so many people
Dialogue: 0,0:37:01.15,0:37:04.02,Default,,0,0,0,,制造出这种口径的机器\N{\fs15\}to come up with a machine of this caliber.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:08.72,0:37:10.79,Default,,0,0,0,,你让这些人为你做这些事\N{\fs15\}You have all these people doing all this stuff for you,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:10.82,0:37:12.96,Default,,0,0,0,,但一旦顶篷关闭…\N{\fs15\}but once that canopy closes...
Dialogue: 0,0:37:12.99,0:37:14.09,Default,,0,0,0,,你准备好了吗\N{\fs15\}MAN: You ready?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:14.13,0:37:15.63,Default,,0,0,0,,罗宾逊：你就靠自己了\N{\fs15\}ROBINSON: You're all alone.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:17.83,0:37:20.90,Default,,0,0,0,,男：45岁  来吧  洛基\N{\fs15\}MAN: 45, hit it, Rocky!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:32.81,0:37:35.12,Default,,0,0,0,,无线电广播：全速  333.9\N{\fs15\}MAN ON RADIO: Full speed, 333.9.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:35.15,0:37:36.75,Default,,0,0,0,,广播员：罗杰  六岁\N{\fs15\}MAN ON RADIO: Roger, six.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:40.85,0:37:43.12,Default,,0,0,0,,罗宾逊：哇  哇  哇\N{\fs15\}ROBINSON: Whoa, whoa, whoa!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:43.16,0:37:45.96,Default,,0,0,0,,发动机出毛病了\N{\fs15\}There's something wrong with the motor.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:45.99,0:37:48.66,Default,,0,0,0,,收音机里的人：他来了……他慢下来了\N{\fs15\}MAN ON RADIO: He's coming to a...he's slowing down.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:50.83,0:37:53.00,Default,,0,0,0,,下面一切都好吗\N{\fs15\}Everything okay down there?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:53.03,0:37:55.60,Default,,0,0,0,,收音机里的人：看起来不错\N{\fs15\}MAN ON RADIO: Seems okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:55.64,0:37:56.60,Default,,0,0,0,,罗宾逊：真的很强劲\N{\fs15\}ROBINSON: It is going really strong,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:56.64,0:37:58.64,Default,,0,0,0,,是的  哇  哇  哇\N{\fs15\}and it's, whoa, whoa, whoa.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:58.67,0:37:59.64,Default,,0,0,0,,男士：请假\N{\fs15\}MAN: Main off?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:59.67,0:38:00.94,Default,,0,0,0,,罗宾逊：是的  男：好的\N{\fs15\}ROBINSON: Yeah. MAN: Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:00.97,0:38:03.81,Default,,0,0,0,,罗宾逊：大约每小时378英里左右\N{\fs15\}ROBINSON: Got up to right around 378 miles an hour,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:03.84,0:38:06.95,Default,,0,0,0,,然后涡轮车钩脱落了\N{\fs15\}and then the turbo coupler came off.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:08.78,0:38:10.68,Default,,0,0,0,,真令人沮丧\N{\fs15\}It's frustrating.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:10.72,0:38:12.12,Default,,0,0,0,,这是一个巨大的团队努力\N{\fs15\}It's a huge team effort,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:12.15,0:38:15.16,Default,,0,0,0,,而且  你知道  我们都在努力实现我们的目标\N{\fs15\}and, you know, we're all trying to reach our goal.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:15.19,0:38:18.49,Default,,0,0,0,,大概95%的时间有问题\N{\fs15\}Probably 95% of the time there is something going wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:18.53,0:38:21.53,Default,,0,0,0,,这就是为什么记录能持续这么久的原因\N{\fs15\}That's why records last so long.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:21.56,0:38:22.83,Default,,0,0,0,,关于陆地速度赛车的一切\N{\fs15\}Everything about land speed racing
Dialogue: 0,0:38:22.86,0:38:26.87,Default,,0,0,0,,学习新事物和改进方法\N{\fs15\}is learning what's new and how to improve things.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:26.90,0:38:29.70,Default,,0,0,0,,我们学到了很多  我想我们可以好好利用它\N{\fs15\}We learn a lot, and I think we can put that to good use
Dialogue: 0,0:38:29.74,0:38:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,未来\N{\fs15\}in the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:33.81,0:38:35.78,Default,,0,0,0,,史密斯：这件事我和洛基在一起\N{\fs15\}SMITH: I'm with Rocky on this.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:35.81,0:38:39.71,Default,,0,0,0,,你被击倒了  你又回来了\N{\fs15\}You get knocked down, you get back up again.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:39.75,0:38:44.42,Default,,0,0,0,,沟通有助于你面对失败而不畏惧\N{\fs15\}Communicating helps you face failure without fear.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:47.55,0:38:49.96,Default,,0,0,0,,但是我们的大脑会适应\N{\fs15\}But our brains adapt.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:49.99,0:38:52.96,Default,,0,0,0,,所以如果我们失去沟通的能力\N{\fs15\}So if we lose the ability to communicate,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:52.99,0:38:57.73,Default,,0,0,0,,我们的大脑可能会找到办法\N{\fs15\}our brain might find a work-around.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:57.76,0:38:59.87,Default,,0,0,0,,它很灵活\N{\fs15\}It's flexible.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:59.90,0:39:01.84,Default,,0,0,0,,和利兰谈谈就知道了\N{\fs15\}Talk to Leland about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:04.77,0:39:05.84,Default,,0,0,0,,梅尔文：在康复期间\N{\fs15\}MELVIN: During the time of recovery
Dialogue: 0,0:39:05.87,0:39:08.81,Default,,0,0,0,,从我的听力事故中\N{\fs15\}from my hearing accident,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:08.84,0:39:13.21,Default,,0,0,0,,有一点我能感觉到我的大脑在重新布线\N{\fs15\}there was a point when I could feel my brain rewiring itself
Dialogue: 0,0:39:13.25,0:39:14.85,Default,,0,0,0,,再听一遍\N{\fs15\}to hear again.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:16.85,0:39:19.92,Default,,0,0,0,,随着时间的推移  大脑可以做出调整\N{\fs15\}The brain over time can make adjustments
Dialogue: 0,0:39:19.95,0:39:24.66,Default,,0,0,0,,赔偿损失或变化\N{\fs15\}to compensate for losses or changes.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:24.69,0:39:27.83,Default,,0,0,0,,我想这就是发生在我身上的事\N{\fs15\}And I think that's what happened to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:27.86,0:39:29.60,Default,,0,0,0,,我的听力开始恢复\N{\fs15\}My hearing started coming back
Dialogue: 0,0:39:29.63,0:39:31.90,Default,,0,0,0,,事故发生三周后\N{\fs15\}about three weeks after my accident.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:33.77,0:39:39.77,Default,,0,0,0,,但我又花了两年时间才恢复正常\N{\fs15\}But it took two more years for me to recover properly.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:39.81,0:39:42.91,Default,,0,0,0,,最后  NASA首席医疗官\N{\fs15\}Then finally, the chief medical officer for NASA
Dialogue: 0,0:39:42.94,0:39:47.05,Default,,0,0,0,,拿出一张纸\N{\fs15\}pulled out a piece of paper
Dialogue: 0,0:39:47.08,0:39:50.48,Default,,0,0,0,,这就是说    你现在可以在太空飞行了\N{\fs15\}that said, 'You are now cleared to fly in space.'
Dialogue: 0,0:39:53.99,0:39:58.76,Default,,0,0,0,,那是我一生中最不可思议的日子之一\N{\fs15\}That was one of the most incredible days of my life.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:58.79,0:40:01.13,Default,,0,0,0,,我再也不认为我的大脑是理所当然的了\N{\fs15\}I never took my brain for granted again.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:05.10,0:40:06.93,Default,,0,0,0,,史密斯：有了灵活的大脑\N{\fs15\}SMITH: With that flexible brain,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:06.97,0:40:11.94,Default,,0,0,0,,我们学习  适应和解决问题\N{\fs15\}we learn, adapt, and problem solve.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:11.97,0:40:15.94,Default,,0,0,0,,我们的大脑给我们语言\N{\fs15\}Our brains give us language,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:15.98,0:40:20.71,Default,,0,0,0,,让我们与他人分享这些教训\N{\fs15\}allowing us to share those lessons with others.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:20.75,0:40:25.65,Default,,0,0,0,,写作让我们通过时间传递知识\N{\fs15\}And writing lets us pass on that knowledge through time.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:29.16,0:40:30.96,Default,,0,0,0,,林格：所有的人类脑力\N{\fs15\}LINENGER: All that human brain power,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:30.99,0:40:34.56,Default,,0,0,0,,所有的知识都通过书面教科书\N{\fs15\}all that knowledge through written textbooks,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:34.60,0:40:37.73,Default,,0,0,0,,通过计算  通过数学\N{\fs15\}through calculations, through mathematics.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:37.76,0:40:40.47,Default,,0,0,0,,霍夫曼：那导致了一场大爆炸\N{\fs15\}HOFFMAN: That just led to a huge explosion
Dialogue: 0,0:40:40.50,0:40:43.04,Default,,0,0,0,,在文明的发展中\N{\fs15\}in the development of civilization.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:45.34,0:40:46.81,Default,,0,0,0,,惠特森：我们可以变得更聪明\N{\fs15\}WHITSON: We can get a lot smarter,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:46.84,0:40:52.81,Default,,0,0,0,,因为我们可以从上一代学到更多\N{\fs15\}because we can learn a lot more from the previous generations.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:52.85,0:40:56.92,Default,,0,0,0,,史密斯：人类是通过思想网络联系在一起的\N{\fs15\}SMITH: Humanity is linked together by a network of minds
Dialogue: 0,0:40:56.95,0:41:00.82,Default,,0,0,0,,跨越时间和空间\N{\fs15\}that spans time and space.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:00.85,0:41:05.79,Default,,0,0,0,,这帮助我们创造了令人眼花缭乱的复杂性\N{\fs15\}And that's helped us create things of dazzling complexity.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:08.03,0:41:13.53,Default,,0,0,0,,我们所做的最复杂的事情就是漂浮在我们的上方\N{\fs15\}The most complex one we've ever made is floating above us.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:22.24,0:41:23.51,Default,,0,0,0,,收音机上的人：点火顺序开始\N{\fs15\}MAN ON RADIO: Ignition sequence start.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:23.54,0:41:27.68,Default,,0,0,0,,五  四  三  二  一\N{\fs15\}Five, four, three, two, one.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:32.02,0:41:35.89,Default,,0,0,0,,梅尔文：你要离开这个星球\N{\fs15\}MELVIN: You're lifting off of the planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:35.92,0:41:37.89,Default,,0,0,0,,感觉胸部有3个重力\N{\fs15\}Feeling 3 Gs on your chest
Dialogue: 0,0:41:37.92,0:41:40.99,Default,,0,0,0,,当你被推进宇宙的时候\N{\fs15\}as you're being propelled to the cosmos.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:41.03,0:41:43.10,Default,,0,0,0,,这真是一次了不起的旅行\N{\fs15\}It is one heck of a ride.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:48.17,0:41:51.47,Default,,0,0,0,,梅尔文：失去听觉后\N{\fs15\}MELVIN: After losing the sense of hearing,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:51.50,0:41:54.47,Default,,0,0,0,,我花了很多年才到达发射台\N{\fs15\}it took so many years for me to get to the launchpad,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:54.51,0:41:58.71,Default,,0,0,0,,但仅仅几分钟就到达了轨道\N{\fs15\}but it just took a few minutes to get to orbit.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:58.75,0:42:01.85,Default,,0,0,0,,广播员：早上好  休斯顿\N{\fs15\}MAN ON RADIO: Good morning, Houston.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:01.88,0:42:04.48,Default,,0,0,0,,梅尔文：我们到了太空  我看到了这个星球\N{\fs15\}MELVIN: We got to space, I saw the planet.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:04.52,0:42:06.62,Default,,0,0,0,,它只会打动你的头脑\N{\fs15\}It just blows your mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:09.02,0:42:13.03,Default,,0,0,0,,这一抹色彩\N{\fs15\}This burst of color.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:13.06,0:42:15.86,Default,,0,0,0,,我从未见过如此鲜艳的色彩\N{\fs15\}I've never seen colors that vibrant before.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:19.73,0:42:23.27,Default,,0,0,0,,我几乎必须  像  拍打自己才能回去工作\N{\fs15\}And I almost had to, like, smack myself to get back to work.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:29.04,0:42:30.54,Default,,0,0,0,,收音机里的人：如果你能找到另一个…\N{\fs15\}MAN ON RADIO: If you could get the other...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:30.58,0:42:33.65,Default,,0,0,0,,探险队的四名队员  我们已经看到他们了\N{\fs15\}the expedition four crew, that we have them in sight.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:36.75,0:42:41.45,Default,,0,0,0,,梅尔文：然后我看到地平线上有一个小点\N{\fs15\}MELVIN: And then I saw this little dot out on the horizon.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:41.49,0:42:44.63,Default,,0,0,0,,我们越来越近了\N{\fs15\}And we get closer and closer and closer.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:51.16,0:42:54.74,Default,,0,0,0,,我第一次看到空间站在上空飞行\N{\fs15\}The first time I saw the space station flying overhead,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:54.77,0:42:59.91,Default,,0,0,0,,我不知道这个飞船有多复杂\N{\fs15\}I never knew how complex a vehicle it was.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:04.81,0:43:07.98,Default,,0,0,0,,你知道  你可以看到复杂的设计\N{\fs15\}You know, you could see the intricate design
Dialogue: 0,0:43:08.01,0:43:10.92,Default,,0,0,0,,在这些模块中  所有这些东西\N{\fs15\}in these modules, all these things
Dialogue: 0,0:43:10.95,0:43:14.96,Default,,0,0,0,,这是人脑想象出来的\N{\fs15\}that were envisioned by the human brain.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:23.86,0:43:25.80,Default,,0,0,0,,惠特森：所以  你知道  当你接近它的时候\N{\fs15\}WHITSON: So, you know, when you approach it,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:25.83,0:43:28.13,Default,,0,0,0,,真是太美了\N{\fs15\}it's just so beautiful.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:28.17,0:43:31.67,Default,,0,0,0,,这是一个令人惊叹的工程奇迹\N{\fs15\}It's an amazing, amazing engineering marvel.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:33.81,0:43:35.84,Default,,0,0,0,,霍夫曼：毫无疑问  太空站\N{\fs15\}HOFFMAN: There's no question that the space station
Dialogue: 0,0:43:35.88,0:43:39.81,Default,,0,0,0,,是最伟大的国际科学项目\N{\fs15\}is the greatest international scientific project
Dialogue: 0,0:43:39.85,0:43:42.82,Default,,0,0,0,,这是有史以来的\N{\fs15\}that's ever been undertaken.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:42.85,0:43:47.12,Default,,0,0,0,,林格：就像  哇  这东西太棒了\N{\fs15\}LINENGER: It's like, wow, this thing is awesome.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:47.15,0:43:48.92,Default,,0,0,0,,我要靠这东西\N{\fs15\}And I'm gonna get to live on that thing
Dialogue: 0,0:43:48.96,0:43:50.66,Default,,0,0,0,,生活四五个月\N{\fs15\}for four or five months.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:56.83,0:43:57.80,Default,,0,0,0,,收音机里的人：现在拿着相机进来了\N{\fs15\}MAN ON RADIO: Coming in now and carrying the camera,
Dialogue: 0,0:43:57.83,0:44:01.63,Default,,0,0,0,,任务专家Leland Melvin\N{\fs15\}mission specialist Leland Melvin.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:01.67,0:44:02.64,Default,,0,0,0,,男：你好吗\N{\fs15\}MAN: How you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:02.67,0:44:03.77,Default,,0,0,0,,老兄 ”公牛闯进了瓷器店“\N{\fs15\}MAN: Bull in a china shop, man.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:12.85,0:44:14.95,Default,,0,0,0,,梅尔文：爬”这座山“到太空\N{\fs15\}MELVIN: Climbing this hill to space
Dialogue: 0,0:44:14.98,0:44:18.95,Default,,0,0,0,,是我做过的最难的事情之一\N{\fs15\}was one of the hardest things I've ever done.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:18.99,0:44:21.55,Default,,0,0,0,,我从没想过自己会聋\N{\fs15\}I never imagined myself going deaf,
Dialogue: 0,0:44:21.59,0:44:22.96,Default,,0,0,0,,我从没想过会回来\N{\fs15\}I never imagined coming back
Dialogue: 0,0:44:22.99,0:44:25.73,Default,,0,0,0,,在那次事故之后得到这个机会\N{\fs15\}and getting this opportunity after that accident.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:31.83,0:44:37.00,Default,,0,0,0,,这对所有人类来说都是一个类似的故事\N{\fs15\}And it's really a similar story for all of humankind.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:37.04,0:44:39.87,Default,,0,0,0,,我们作为一个物种所取得的一切\N{\fs15\}Everything we've achieved as a species
Dialogue: 0,0:44:39.91,0:44:43.74,Default,,0,0,0,,是一系列幸运事故的产物\N{\fs15\}is the product of a lucky chain of accidents.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:48.11,0:44:52.69,Default,,0,0,0,,史密斯：要到这里  我们需要一颗行星从尘埃中凝结出来\N{\fs15\}SMITH: To get here, we needed a planet to congeal out of dust.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:54.89,0:45:00.43,Default,,0,0,0,,在生命形成和塑造我们世界的正确地方\N{\fs15\}In the right place for life to form and mold our world,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:00.46,0:45:04.36,Default,,0,0,0,,让我们呼吸并变得复杂\N{\fs15\}allowing us to breathe and grow complex.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:07.20,0:45:11.77,Default,,0,0,0,,我们需要避开太阳\N{\fs15\}We needed to be shielded from our sun,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:11.81,0:45:14.91,Default,,0,0,0,,有月亮的恩赐\N{\fs15\}gifted with a moon,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:14.94,0:45:17.54,Default,,0,0,0,,以及季节的授予\N{\fs15\}and granted seasons.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:17.58,0:45:19.91,Default,,0,0,0,,我们只需要足够的轰炸\N{\fs15\}We needed just enough bombardments
Dialogue: 0,0:45:19.95,0:45:21.45,Default,,0,0,0,,几乎湮灭\N{\fs15\}and near-annihilations
Dialogue: 0,0:45:21.48,0:45:23.45,Default,,0,0,0,,让生命漫步\N{\fs15\}to let life meander
Dialogue: 0,0:45:23.48,0:45:25.55,Default,,0,0,0,,通过它的曲折\N{\fs15\}through its twists and turns
Dialogue: 0,0:45:25.59,0:45:28.12,Default,,0,0,0,,进化出一个物种\N{\fs15\}and evolve a species
Dialogue: 0,0:45:28.15,0:45:33.13,Default,,0,0,0,,像你我一样复杂的大脑\N{\fs15\}with a brain as complex as yours and mine.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:41.84,0:45:43.77,Default,,0,0,0,,梅尔文：我在空间站的时候\N{\fs15\}MELVIN: When I was on the space station,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:43.80,0:45:47.74,Default,,0,0,0,,回首地球\N{\fs15\}looking back at the planet,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:47.77,0:45:52.95,Default,,0,0,0,,我对它抱着深刻的谢意\N{\fs15\}it gave me a profound appreciation
Dialogue: 0,0:45:52.98,0:45:55.58,Default,,0,0,0,,在我们认为理所当然的事情上\N{\fs15\}in what we take for granted.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:58.65,0:46:02.92,Default,,0,0,0,,人类是一个奇妙的  非凡的怪人\N{\fs15\}Humans are a wonderful, extraordinary oddity.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:07.93,0:46:10.16,Default,,0,0,0,,史密斯：干得好  伙计  很棒的游戏\N{\fs15\}SMITH: Good job, man, great game.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:10.20,0:46:13.00,Default,,0,0,0,,有了这个果冻\N{\fs15\}With this blob of Jell-O,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:13.03,0:46:17.64,Default,,0,0,0,,860亿神经元\N{\fs15\}these 86 billion neurons,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:17.67,0:46:19.97,Default,,0,0,0,,我们可以离开这个星球\N{\fs15\}we've left the planet
Dialogue: 0,0:46:20.01,0:46:23.74,Default,,0,0,0,,远眺宇宙\N{\fs15\}and looked far, far out into the universe,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:23.78,0:46:28.51,Default,,0,0,0,,试图揭开宇宙的奥秘\N{\fs15\}trying to unravel the mysteries of the cosmos.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:28.55,0:46:31.65,Default,,0,0,0,,但不管我们看地有多遥远\N{\fs15\}But no matter how far out we look,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:31.68,0:46:34.59,Default,,0,0,0,,我们发现的最遥远的东西\N{\fs15\}the most far-out thing we've ever found
Dialogue: 0,0:46:34.62,0:46:36.79,Default,,0,0,0,,就在我们耳边\N{\fs15\}is right between our ears.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:50.20,0:46:52.17,Default,,0,0,0,,下一次\N{\fs15\}Next time...
Dialogue: 0,0:46:52.21,0:46:56.64,说明,,0,0,0,,当你最终回到地球时  感觉如何\N{\fs15\}What does it feel like when you finally come back to Earth?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:56.68,0:46:59.51,说明,,0,0,0,,真的没有像家这样的地方吗\N{\fs15\}Is there really no place like home?
        
